           <span class="uitext reviewText">history buffs and action fans</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer16576281" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14882471432157565078">If Tom Clancy and Casablanca had a love child, it&apos;d be this book, and it&apos;s a great read. More action and faced-paced suspense than Casablanca, more emotional depth than Clancy. But at the same time, it has both their drawbacks as well -- too many characters with interchangeable Russian and German names, and it depends on the reader having a healthy knowledge of the history of WWII in order to understand the story. <br/><br/>Still, I enjoyed the mystery and intrigue in the story, and Kanon&apos;s portrayal of p</span>
  <span id="freeText14882471432157565078" style="display:none">If Tom Clancy and Casablanca had a love child, it'd be this book, and it's a great read. More action and faced-paced suspense than Casablanca, more emotional depth than Clancy. But at the same time, it has both their drawbacks as well -- too many characters with interchangeable Russian and German names, and it depends on the reader having a healthy knowledge of the history of WWII in order to understand the story. <br /><br />Still, I enjoyed the mystery and intrigue in the story, and Kanon's portrayal of postwar Berlin was nuanced and moving.</span>
